OL,6,F"So, as we all celebrate the end of
OL,7,Fthis chapter, we must remember the
OL,8,Fpower education has in transforming
OL,9,Flives, and, more importantly, the
OL,10,Fprivileges we hold and the
OL,11,Fresponsibilities we bear in ensuring
OL,12,Fthat these opportunities are available
OL,13,Fto all."
OL,15,FGrowing up in west London, Miss Chopra
OL,16,Fwould read the family's post, fill out
OL,17,Ftheir forms and read books to her
OL,18,Fbrother and sister.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
