OL,4,Cflees Taliban
OL,6,FShe believes those childhood
OL,7,Fexperiences shaped her studies and
OL,8,Fhelped propel her towards a career in
OL,9,Flaw.
OL,11,F"In their youth, my parents weren't
OL,12,Freally allowed to participate in
OL,13,Feducation," she said.
OL,15,F"My grandfather died young and my dad
OL,16,Fhad to work, and there was a cultural
OL,17,Felement of what a woman's place was.
OL,18,FDespite that, they've always seen the
OL,19,Fvalue in education.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
